@database Printer_PrimeraPro.guide

@node Main "Printer:  PrimeraPro"

   One of the most interesting color printers in the marketplace is the
new PrimeraPro, from Fargo, Inc.  The PrimeraPro produces high-quality
thermal wax transfer or dye sublimation color images at a very affordable
price.  One of its drawbacks, however, is that it requires the computer
driving it to do almost all of the work.

   To print using the PrimeraPro, ImageFX must compose the entire print
page in memory and send the data, all in one continuous chunk, to the
printer.  For large images, this can require a great deal of RAM.
Fortunately, you can use ImageFX's Virtual Memory system when printing
to PrimeraPro printers.

   You should not attempt to print a Landscape oriented image
(horizontally, across the widest page dimension) on the PrimeraPro.
Instead, use the 2D Rotation controls in the Transform menu to turn the
image 90 degrees and print using the Portrait orientation.

   Refer, as necessary, to the documentation on the Primera and PrimeraPro
printer for details concerning the PrimeraPro configuration options.

@endnode
